Vol / Page:  27
Edition:
Quote:   ... the track to Aicken through the bush was not cut originally to assist trampers and mountaineers, but was made for the purpose of providing a way for a pipe line used during the constructional work on the tunnel. <i>Ibid.</i> 59 The place is a strategic base for mountaineers who wish to conquer the peaks at the head of the Waimakariri, and for trampers on the `Three Pass Trip' (see Harman Pass) it makes a convenient resting place.
